BEGIN_PGML
Write an inequality to model the scenario. There is no need to solve the inequality.

An airplane was cruising at [`[$start]\text{,}`] and then began its descent. Because of some air traffic congestion, it will descend to [`[$end]`] and then circle the airport for a while. It descends at a rate of [`[$speed]\text{.}`] A passenger notices the plane is still descending. Set up an inequality where the solution set represents how much time might have passed since the plane started its descent. There is no need to solve it.

[@KeyboardInstructions('Use [|t|]* as the variable.')@]**

[_]{$inequality}{20}

END_PGML

