BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
This is a rate exercise, and we can use

[```
                  (\text{initial value}) \pm (\text{rate})\cdot\text{variable} \mathrel{?} (\text{final value})
                ```]

The question mark in the above is not an equal sign, because we are trying to set up an inequality. The initial value for the altitude is [`[$initial]\text{,}`] the altitude is decreasing (so we will subtract, not add), the rate is [`[$rate]\text{,}`] and the final altitude is [`[$final]\text{.}`] We do not know is how much time has passed, so we decide to use [`t`] to represent that time. At the moment the passenger makes their observation, the plane is still descending, so the altitude is greater than the final value. So our inequality is:

